
• Implemented the portal visual/occlusion fix.

  The portal now uses one visible animated state sprite:

  - idle is the default visible state.
  - source portal plays activate.
  - destination portal plays arrival.
  - both return to idle.
  - the static portal base sprite is hidden for portal props so the animation no longer stacks over a second rendered portal.

  Key code:

  - custodian/game/world/procgen/portal_teleporter.gd
  - custodian/game/world/procgen/proc_gen_tilemap.gd

  Occlusion change:

  - Portal depth now uses the portal platform top as the horizon.
  - Operator draws in front when below the plateau.
  - Portal draws in front when the operator is at/above the plateau.

  Docs updated:

  - custodian/docs/ai_context/CURRENT_STATE.md
  - custodian/docs/ai_context/FILE_INDEX.md
  - custodian/docs/ai_context/task_packets/PORTAL_DUAL_APPROACH_TUNING.md
  - design/02_features/props/PROCEDURAL_PROP_VARIANT_SYSTEM.md

  Validation passed:

  - portal_teleporter.gd
  - proc_gen_tilemap.gd
  - ProceduralProp.gd

  Residual tuning risk: the exact plateau line may need a few pixels of adjustment in play, but the rule is now correct and tunable.

  Current focus: single-instance portal animation and plateau occlusion. Last session completed: portal state playback now replaces the
  stacked duplicate animation path. Next items: playtest portal approach from both sides, then tune collision/ramp offsets once the
  occlusion read is stable.
